Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Place a few @salad potatoes{500%g} at a time in between two #wooden spoon handles{} on a #cutting board{}. Make slices widthways at 3mm intervals, making sure not to cut the whole way through. Repeat with the remaining potatoes.

Put the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%pinch}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{35-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

About 15 mins before the potatoes are ready, remove the tray from the oven and move the potatoes to one side.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto the other side of the baking tray. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast for the remaining time until the salmon is cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} and shallot. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of @water{splash} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Allow to cook until the veg is tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more, then stir through the @wholegrain mustard{17%g} until well combined.

Spoon the mustard broccoli and shallot into a #bowl{}, then cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe the frying pan clean.

When the salmon and potatoes are almost ready, return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat.

Pour in the @water{75%ml}(for the sauce), @creme fraiche{75%g} and @fresh pesto{50%g}. Stir well and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2%minutes}.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, share the baked salmon and hasselback potatoes between your plates.

Spoon the creamy pesto sauce over the salmon, then serve with the mustard shallots and broccoli alongside.

Enjoy!

> Due to quality issues with leek, you'll instead receive echalion shallot. As such, the recipe photos are slightly different to what your dish will look like. Don't worry, we've updated the instructions so it'll still be just as delicious!

> This Roasted Salmon and Creamy Pesto Sauce is a luxurious dinner night option, made with premium ingredients for a real taste of luxury at home!